## Backfill note (added 2026-04-26 retroactively)

## Conversation
Three live bugs in team-prompts subsystem (PR #46): turn display
off-by-one at turn_idx=0, auto-skip never fires, submit_team_phrase
silently drops writes. Filed as #58.

## Actions
- Root caused (a): client sorted writing-team roster by display_name,
  server's `team_prompting_roster()` orders by joined_at. Mismatch on
  non-alphabetical join orders. Fix: fetch joined_at on every
  room_players query and sort client roster by (joined_at, player_id).
- Root caused (b): `skip_team_turn` had a 1s slack on its expiry guard
  rejecting the host's first RPC at the zero-crossing; client effect
  swallowed the error. Fix: drop slack server-side (client already
  rounds with Math.ceil) AND replace fire-and-forget with 1s polling
  retry while turn is overdue. Also added expired-turn fast-forward
  inside `submit_team_phrase`.
- Root caused (c): RPC was raising exceptions but server logs were
  empty. Added `RAISE NOTICE 'submit_team_phrase rejected: ...'` before
  every exception so Vercel runtime logs surface reasons.
- Migration 20260420160100_team_prompts_hardening.sql.

